This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with visual data such as videos. It also involves deep learning techniques, which suggests that it could belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper evaluates its proposed approach on benchmark datasets, which could indicate that it belongs to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of the Alternating Direction Method of Multipliers and Backward Propagation (ADMM-BP) suggests that it could also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
